        <article class="post-2168 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-environment category-video tag-forest-service tag-international-programs tag-lima tag-logging tag-peru tag-pucallpa tag-serfor tag-timber tag-u-s-forest-service et_pb_post" id="post-2168">
         <h2>
          <a href="http://eliegardner.com/2015/02/21/u-s-forest-service-in-peru/">
           u.s. forest service in peru
          </a>
         </h2>
        </article>
        <p class="post-meta">
         by
         <a rel="author" title="Posts by Elie" href="http://eliegardner.com/author/admin/">
          Elie
         </a>
         | Feb 21, 2015 |
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in blog" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/blog/">
          blog
         </a>
         ,
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in environment" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/environment/">
          environment
         </a>
         ,
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in video" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/video/">
          video
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         Last fall
         <a href="http://jordangantz.com">
          Jordan Gantz
         </a>
         and I told the story of how the U.S. Forest Service helped Peru develop an information system for tracking wood harvested from the Amazon. The trip included my first visit to a saw mill, interaction with many hardworking and inspiring people and lots of mosquito bites.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="https://vimeo.com/115110011">
          [See the Spanish version of the video here.]
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         <div class="fluid-width-video-wrapper" style="padding-top: 56.25%;">
          <iframe frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" src="//player.vimeo.com/video/115060204?color=ffffff&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&amp;wmode=opaque" id="fitvid162615">
          </iframe>
         </div>
        </p>
