        <article class="post-2107 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog category-environment category-travel category-video tag-conservation tag-environment tag-mongabay tag-tambopata tag-tourism et_pb_post" id="post-2107">
         <h2>
          <a href="http://eliegardner.com/2015/02/01/community-tourism-near-tambopata/">
           community tourism along the tambopata river
          </a>
         </h2>
        </article>
        <p class="post-meta">
         by
         <a rel="author" title="Posts by Elie" href="http://eliegardner.com/author/admin/">
          Elie
         </a>
         | Feb 1, 2015 |
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in blog" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/blog/">
          blog
         </a>
         ,
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in environment" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/environment/">
          environment
         </a>
         ,
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in travel" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/travel/">
          travel
         </a>
         ,
         <a rel="category tag" title="View all posts in video" href="http://eliegardner.com/category/video/">
          video
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         Last fall I had the opportunity to travel for a few days down the Tambopata River with Barbara Fraser to tell this story for Mongabay.
         <a href="http://news.mongabay.com/2015/0129-sri-fraser-tourism-tambopata.html">
          Read Barb’s full story here
         </a>
         .
        </p>
